        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): add sessions_delegate and sessions_delegate_batch tools",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n- Problem: OpenClaw agents can spawn background sessions (`sessions_spawn`) but cannot synchronously delegate a task and receive structured output back as a tool result. Complex parallelizable work runs sequentially or requires manual user coordination.\r\n\r\n- Why it matters: Multi-agent orchestration (fan-out/fan-in, map-reduce, pipeline patterns) is blocked without a synchronous delegation primitive.\r\n\r\n- What changed:\r\n\r\n  - Added `sessions_delegate` tool — blocking spawn-and-wait that returns child output as a tool result\r\n\r\n  - Added `sessions_delegate_batch` tool — parallel fan-out of multiple delegate tasks with configurable failure mode\r\n\r\n  - Wired up the existing but unused `prepareSubagentSpawn` context engine hook in `subagent-spawn.ts`\r\n\r\n  - Registered both tools in tool catalog, display config, and openclaw-tools\r\n\r\n- What did NOT change (scope boundary): `sessions_spawn` behavior is untouched. No changes to auto-announce, session lanes, or existing lifecycle hooks. No plugin-layer orchestration patterns yet (map-reduce, pipeline, race) — this PR provides the runtime primitives only.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Change Type\r\n\r\n- [ ] Bug fix\r\n- [x] Feature\r\n- [ ] Refactor required for the fix\r\n- [ ] Docs\r\n- [ ] Security hardening\r\n- [ ] Chore/infra\r\n\r\n## Scope\r\n\r\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\r\n- [x] Skills / tool execution\r\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\r\n- [ ] Memory / storage\r\n- [ ] Integrations\r\n- [x] API / contracts\r\n- [ ] UI / DX\r\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\r\n\r\n\r\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\r\n\r\n- Two new agent tools available: `sessions_delegate` and `sessions_delegate_batch`\r\n- `sessions_delegate`: spawns a child agent, blocks until completion, returns output directly as tool result (default timeout 120s, default cleanup \"delete\")\r\n- `sessions_delegate_batch`: fans out 1–10 tasks in parallel, returns collected results with per-task status and summary. `failureMode: \"partial\"` (default) returns completed results even if some fail; `\"all\"` fails the batch if any task fails.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Diagram (if applicable)\r\n\r\n```text\r\n\r\n**Before (sessions_spawn):**\r\n\r\n[parent calls sessions_spawn] -> [child runs async] -> [auto-announce as user message] -> [parent resumes on next turn]\r\n\r\n**After (sessions_delegate):**\r\n\r\n[parent calls sessions_delegate] -> [child runs] -> [tool blocks via agent.wait] -> [reads frozenResultText] -> [returns as tool result in same turn]\r\n\r\n**After (sessions_delegate_batch):**\r\n\r\n[parent calls sessions_delegate_batch] -> [N children spawn] -> [Promise.allSettled] -> [collect results] -> [return aggregated tool result]\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Security Impact (required)\r\n\r\n- New permissions/capabilities? `Yes` — two new agent tools, but they reuse existing `spawnSubagentDirect` which enforces depth limits, active children limits, sandbox policies, and visibility guards.\r\n- Secrets/tokens handling changed? `No`\r\n- New/changed network calls? `No` — reuses existing `agent.wait` gateway RPC\r\n- Command/tool execution surface changed? `Yes` — new tools registered in catalog\r\n- Data access scope changed? `No`\r\n- Risk + mitigation: New tools inherit all existing spawn guards (max depth, max active children, sandbox mode, session lane isolation). No new escalation paths.\r\n\r\n## Compatibility / Migration\r\n\r\n- Backward compatible? `Yes`\r\n- Config/env changes? `No`\r\n- Migration needed? `No`",
